  <a href="#0" id="0">
   We replace the overlap mechanism of the Lesk algorithm with a simple, general-purpose Naive Bayes model that measures many-to-many association between two sets of random variables.
  </a>
  <a href="#1" id="1">
   Even with simple probability estimates such as maximum likelihood, the model gains significant improvement over the Lesk algorithm on word sense disambiguation tasks.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   With additional lexical knowledge from WordNet, performance is further improved to surpass the state-of-the-art results.
  </a>
